<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>hard at it • hard put to it</xh5><p> <i>hard at it—</i>very busy; working industriously: When we got to the field, the farmer and his son were already <u>hard at it</u>.</p><p><i>hard put to it—</i>find it very difficult to do smth.: Developing countries are <u>hard put to it</u> to raise the capital even for cheaper, though more pollutive, technologies.</p> </entry>
